<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9776999409201></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9776999409201><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9776999409201>RE: Pets??</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9776999409201#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9251><span id=Scholar>Martinet</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>22 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 24th 11:19 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well... there are several posts on this forum and as well as on other web sites concerning the pet-xp question.<br>So this what they say:<br>Pets take 50% of the xp if they do more damage than the mage (common from lvls 4 to 8... but unlikely after that since you get some good dd spells at lvl 8)<br><br>Pets take NO xp if the mage does more damage than the pet<br><br>AND pets don't take any xp in groups<br><br>Hope this helps a bit ;)&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Martinet Morgentau,<br>Gretelchen </td></tr>
