	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is sorta a good strategy but...<br>doing that much dmg to a monster will totally make it focus on you.&nbsp;&nbsp;With that in mind, you'll be left running in circles while your pet is trying and trying to pull it off you, but it can't because you have aggroed it with that wave of 2 bolts.  Well your pet will eventually pull it off but the dmg will leave you with more downtime.  And mostly at higher lvls, if you pull a monster with two shots of a bolt (or Projectile), well dam, these high lvl monsters will eat you alive with only maybe 9 shots (and they usually quad hit too).  With that in mind your pet won't even really get a chance to pull it off (unless this certain monster has some weird aggro way).<br>Take DreadLands for instance, I did the double projectile thing, bam, I'm running around in circles for some time with a Spider whacking me in the 80s.<br>I usually pull with a low DD (Blaze (it's not really low but it's kinda low compared to my other DDs I got)),  or Malisement (too bad Malosi fizzles too much).<br>Either way ok, this is just another OPINION.  Some may agree with this while others won't, but anyways just have fun and try not to die (unless you find fun in dying or something...).<br><br>-Ryyal<br><br>P.S. It's kinda late right now so plz tell me if I made no sense or if I had a few typos on something.. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
