	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am currently a 26 mage and I admit that I was looking forward to using Swords of Runes.&nbsp;&nbsp;I was extremely pissed off when I read that they didn't proc on anything anymore.  Then I remembered what I said to the melee classes who moaned when they fixed the haste stacking bug.  I remember saying, "It's not a nerf, they just fixed a bug."<br>Now it makes no sense for Ward Summoned to proc on everything.  They fixed a long lasting bug that eventually would have to be fixed.<br><br>I'm not really experienced at high levels so take it with a grain of salt, but I am not seeing the 40 damage from the sword doing much good against things with a couple thousand hp.<br><br>As for nerfing the pet dex, they didn't.  The pet dex has always been the same LOW number.  Pets just had an insane chance to proc.  Now that they proc based on dex, we see that our pets' dex has been screwed for a long time.  10 to 1 Verant decides it isn't important enough to fix.<br><br>Now don't think I am not pissed at the nerf, I am just resigned and know it won't go back to the way things used to be.<br><br>If I were high level I'd think I'd go have a blast at the best of the best, think about it has Verant ever changed anything because of what we do?<br><br>Denevian Gerosilex<br>26th Mage<br>Cazic-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br>34th Mage of Cazic-Thule<br>Member of The Chosen Elite<br>25th Druid of The Nameless<br></td></tr>
